What have you been doing?' 'Nothing,' replied Luzhin. 'And what are you planning to do now?' asked Luzhin senior in the same tone of forced jollity, imitating his son's manner of using the formal plural for

'you'. 'Do you want to go to bed or do you want to sit here with me?'

